## Waste Management and Sanitation Analysis

---

## 1. Analysis Areas
- Infrastructure availability  
- Service coverage  
- Environmental risk zones  
- Operational gaps  

---

## 2. Data Analysis

| Parameter | Observation | Gap |
|-----------|------------|-----|
| Waste Bins | Limited | Expansion required |
| Waste Tanks | None | Major infrastructure gap |
| WASH Facilities | Limited | Public health concern |
| Collection Services | Inconsistent | Efficiency gap |

---

## 3. Key Findings
- Waste infrastructure does not meet demand  
- Environmental risks linked to poor drainage and dumping  
- WASH facilities are inadequate  
- Service delivery lacks consistency  

---

## 4. Conclusion
Significant gaps exist in waste management systems. Strategic interventions are required to improve sanitation and environmental conditions.
